body:
> @csantanapr please review -- in particular how do we keep this doc in sync with bluemix docs these days?

@sjfink Once it get's review and accepted/merge in this repo, I will semi-manually sync and send a PR to  [IBM-Bluemix/docs](https://github.com/IBM-Bluemix/docs) with the new updates.
There is not easy programmatically one way sync from open to bluemix docs two different formats

that is the logs field, which points exactly at the problem, whereas the response field has

```
    "response": {
        "result": {
            "error": "the action did not return a dictionary"
        },
        "status": "action developer error",
        "success": false
    },
```

@JacopoMangiavacchi Thanks for posting a comment, 
Once there is a simple objectstore write and read actions, then is open to be use to compose solutions, like you describe. to take out the attachment (i.e. photo, mp3, pdf, etc..) and write it to object store with the action. 

The action can be invoke directly or indirectly thru an event, or just have a single action that does multiple things on a single cloudant change event, it can process the doc including transferring the attachment  to objectstore using the objectstore api, and adding a reference to the file in objectstore item back in the cloudant doc.
